values: Do I even dare to use this thing anymore?

reading back on some of my first entries in this, wow, I have changed so much. I am not young and naive anymore. not so aggressive. it appears that I have toned down in my old years.

it's hard to believe that was even me. when these days I can't even be bothered to feel much like myself. seeing as I am a victim of identity theft. someone used my identity when they were arrested for dealing heroin. so I have this criminal charge against my name. it's irking and rather unsettling. i'm so paranoid. I already have awful trust issues. this is just icing on the cake. always looking over my shoulder.

in other, more uplifting news, I will be going to centralia pennsylvania this saturday. the abandoned town that silent hill was based off of. this should be rather eye-opening.
MY CAR GOT STOLEN TODAY, ALONG WITH MY CELL PHONE, CREDIT CARDS, AND LICENSE, ALL RIGHT IN FRONT OF MY WORK.
I'm slowly trying to dig myself out of this hole I've been in for close to a year now.
life has become an interesting thing to overcome as of late.

<lj-cut>I know it has been a really long time since I last journaled at all, anywhere. There is just so much flowing through me right now that I feel that I must share with the world.

First off, I am now 25 years old and feel as if I am at the prime of my years. This doesn't mean that I feel old, though I am starting to feel my age, though I may not be showing it quite yet. I thought I would never find someone that I would consider my soul mate, but I feel that I may have. It's really incredible and too real and scary all at the same time. My life lately has been more focused on keeping me sane and trying to really become more self-suffient. Lots of things are starting to look up for me and I just don't know how to make sense of it all.

His name is Brett and the connection I personally feel towards him makes no sense on any normal scale. It really makes no sense. We just make sense together.  I guess it doesn't make sense unless you have experienced what I am experiencing. But the energy that I feel towards him, there's like some sort of magnetism that draws us in so close. He's admitted from the beginning, all the time. I've just have taken my time in realizing this for some reason. 

See, I just moved back home back in the middle of August. It was pretty much the end of a relationship that I was in for over a year and a half. I really think it technically ended back when he left to move to Florida. I met Brett the end of August at the college. Of course I thought that he was great and all that, someone that I definitely wanted to get to know better, but because I was still "taken," and to be on the safe side, I just held back. We were friends on facebook and would periodically chat. From the beginning, there was definitely about him, now that I think back on it. I can definitely say that I was drawn to him right from the beginning. I didn't want to go further just because you never know what might happen and plus it might have looked weird, and from what has happened thus far between us, I think it is pretty much self-explanatory. 

But for now, for tonight, I think that I am done with this entry. More will be posted later. I have to get it all down and outside of my head. And perhaps reminisce about the bigger picture. So goodnight.</lj>
